The twelve (12) member board shall be appointed to two (2) year terms, initially appointed by the Governor, and composed of the following members:
Three (3) representatives from postsecondary institutions;
One (1) representative from the Council for Social Sciences;
Six (6) representatives from elementary and secondary schools;
One (1) representative of the Department of Education; and
One (1) representative of the Council on Postsecondary Education.
